James Johnstone (4 July 1801 – 24 February 1888) was a Scottish Liberal Party politician.
He was the oldest of 8 sons of James Raymond Johnstone (died 1830) of Alva, who was the son of John Johnstone (1734–1795).He was elected at a by-election in June 1851 as the Member of Parliament (MP) for Clackmannanshire and Kinross-shire.
He was returned unopposed in 1852, and did not contest the 1857 election.
